Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced on Page 03
And	I'm on Page 06 of Feet MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Diseases of the MTP' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'D1' radio button is enabled
And 'Plantar plate rupture' radio button is enabled


When I select 'D1' radio button
Then 'Hallux-Valgus' radio button is enabled
And 'Sesamoid bones' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Hallux-Valgus' radio button
Then 'Hallux alignment relative to 1st metatarsal' input field is enabled
And 'Intermetatarsal angle' input field is enabled
And 'Lateral deviation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral dislocation of the sesamoid bones' checkbox is enabled
And 'Proliferation sesamoid bones' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subluxation in the 1st metatarsophalangeal joint' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovial enhancement' checkbox is enabled
And 'Accompanying bursitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Medial pseudoexostosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'D5' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Sesamoid bones' radio button
Then 'Medial' radio button is enabled
And 'Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'Sesamoiditis' radio button is enabled
And 'Osteonecrosis' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Plantar plate rupture' radio button
Then 'D1' checkbox is enabled
And 'D2' checkbox is enabled
And 'D3' checkbox is enabled
And 'D4' checkbox is enabled
And 'D5' checkbox is enabled

And 'Distal, base of proximal phalanx' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal, metatarsal head' radio button is enabled
And 'Osseous avulsion fracture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'D1' checkbox
Then 'Extension into collateral ligaments' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pericapsular fibrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Metatarsophalangeal dislocation' checkbox is enabled
And 'Adjacent ganglion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Adjacent ganglion' checkbox
Then 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled
